
                                            Mahlangu does not appear on the arbitration witness list despite being at the centre of the Esidimeni tragedy.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - The Democratic Alliance (DA) in Gauteng says former health MEC Qedani Mahlangu can now be subpoenaed to appear before the Esidimeni arbitration hearings following confirmations that she’s reportedly studying at the London School of Economics. The party says the university can provide justice Dikgang Moseneke with her London address and be subpoenaed to appear before the hearings as they're due to conclude this week. It’s emerged Mahlangu flew from South Africa to London in July. Mahlangu does not appear on the arbitration witness list despite being at the centre of the Esidimeni tragedy. She authorised the transfer of thousands of patients from Life Esidimeni to various NGOs leading to 141 deaths since last year The DA's Jack Bloom said, “The should set the legal process to ensure that she testifies. The relatives of the patients are all unanimous that she should testify, she was the one who was most responsible for the Esidimeni tragedy.”